 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Dalamarn Darkgem</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Fear kiting is mainly an outdoors only technique.  You can get in SERIOUS trouble trying it in dungeons.  </P><P>Easiest way, as stated, is to pull with darkness, send in pet, fear, then reapply darkness/fear as necessary.  The heart flutter line is good to throw in as well as it drops their melee stats.  Lifetap to replace life until you get the vampiric embrace line  (lifetap over time like a DOT spell).  </P><P>Also, try to melee some.  Step in and take a few hits, then step out and lifetap to replace them.  This will build up your defense and dodge skills which will help you A LOT later in life.</P><P> </font></td>
